premise_source_doc_sentence: In an `` engineering '' sense , a chemical process is a method intended to be used in manufacturing or on an industrial scale  (  see Industrial process  )  to change the composition of chemical  (  s  )  or material  (  s  )  , usually using technology similar or related to that used in chemical plants or the chemical industry .

Process safety focuses on preventing fires , explosions and accidental chemical releases in chemical process facilities or other facilities dealing with hazardous materials such as refineries , and oil and gas  (  onshore and offshore  )  production installations .
More than one chemical plant may use the same chemical process , each plant perhaps at differently scaled capacities .
In a scientific sense , a chemical process is a method or means of somehow changing one or more chemicals or chemical compounds .
Such a chemical process can occur by itself or be caused by an outside force , and involves a chemical reaction of some sort .
